              "blockId": "cb-q1",
              "type": "text",
              "content": "We're built to remember stories, not base rates. A friend's terrible flight cancels out a statistic about the safest year in aviation history. Good judgment means consciously re-weighting the dry number above the vivid tale."
            },
            {
              "blockId": "cb-q2",
              "type": "audio",
              "url": "",
              "captionOrTranscript": "Transcript: A two-minute clip discusses how a single recalled shark attack reshapes beach attendance for an entire summer, despite the vanishingly small change in actual risk."
            },
